    "body": "I figured it out. When you define a network called `development` it tries to use that for testing. I confirmed that by looking at the code for the CLI here:\r\nhttps://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/core/lib/commands/test/run.js\r\n\r\nIf I comment out the entire network section in the config it uses an internal Ganache instance.\r\n\r\nThe point I was trying to make was I have to comment/uncomment that section to run `truffle test` vs `truffle migrate`",
