    "body": "Yes, @joeax but there are some catches here. `truffle test` and `truffle migrate` both uses `development` as the default network if it is specified in the `truffle-config.js`. But `truffle test` starts a Ganache instance if no network is specified in the config. Whereas, `truffle migrate` needs a network specification in the config. For that, you can either give the network specification in the `development` network or you can specify your required network in the config and use the `--network` option with `truffle migrate` to deploy the contracts into that network, something like -\r\n`truffle migrate --network <network_name>`",
